==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scapegoat
<hw>Scape"goat`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Scape</ets>
(for <ets>escape</ets>) + <ets>goat</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Jewish Antiq.)</fld> <def>A goat upon whose head were symbolically
placed the sins of the people, after which he was suffered to escape
into the wilderness.</def> <rj><au>Lev. xvi. 10.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, a person or thing that is made to bear blame
for others.</def> <rj><au>Tennyson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scapegrace</ent>⟦br⟧
